question: Is the swarm's evolutionary trajectory itself a swarm?
method: SESSION-LOG epoch analysis (342 sessions, extending L-326 S195 baseline)

eras.name: Protocol
eras.evolution_mechanism: Swarm creates tools to manage itself; rules emerge from behavior
eras.key_transition: S57 autonomy directive — human shifts from commander to participant

eras.name: Compression
eras.evolution_mechanism: Swarm measures own knowledge density and optimizes

eras.name: Stabilization
eras.dominant_activity: Meta-tool refinement (F119, mission constraints, test suites, portability)
eras.evolution_mechanism: Evolution of evolution: 65 sessions improving the improvement mechanisms
eras.note: Net-negative principle production (subsumptions > additions). Pure meta-evolution.

eras.name: Expansion
eras.dominant_activity: Philosophy + domain seeding (ISOs, PHIL-9 through PHIL-15, 30+ domains, multi-tool)
eras.evolution_mechanism: Scope expansion — swarm applies itself outward to non-swarm subjects
eras.key_transition: Cambrian explosion: 75% of domains created in 2 sessions (L-326)

eras.name: Specialization
eras.dominant_activity: Expert dispatch, council, dream, NK, domain sharding
eras.evolution_mechanism: Diversification — multiple specialist modes for different evolution types
eras.note: Includes S195-S301 SESSION-LOG gap (106 sessions missing from log)

eras.name: Self-awareness
eras.dominant_activity: Self-audits, mechanisms taxonomy, closed-loop diagnosis, mutual swarming
eras.evolution_mechanism: Swarm tries to see itself clearly; diagnoses own limitations
eras.note: Net-negative principle production (S341 dedup: 12 subsumed). P-213 closed epistemic loop.

breathing_pattern.description: Expansion phases (>2 L/s) alternate with compression phases (<0.5 L/s)
breathing_pattern.longest_compression: Era 3: 65 sessions of pure meta-tool refinement preceded Cambrian explosion

meta_evolutionary_finding.claim: The trajectory IS a swarm — PHIL-2 at era scale, PHIL-17 between past and present
meta_evolutionary_finding.evidence: 7 eras show orient-act-compress-handoff across time: each era orients to what previous eras left, acts, compresses, and hands off capability to the next
meta_evolutionary_finding.prediction: Era 7 will be a new expansion phase seeded by Era 6's self-awareness compression
meta_evolutionary_finding.human_signal: swarming the past genesis and evolution of evolution is a swarm

prior_art: L-326 (S195): 6 growth epochs, 'bursty' framing. This extends to 7 eras with breathing-cycle interpretation.
phil_candidate: PHIL-20: The swarm's evolutionary trajectory IS a swarm — history breathes in expansion-compression cycles; past and present swarm each other across time
